      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1936: 🔴 When IPv6 is promoted to primary (IPv6-only fallback), `accountLocalAddr6` and `accountPublicAddr6` are not cleared. This means `ice_transport.cpp:515-516` will see both primary and secondary as IPv6 (same family), suppressing the IPv6 SRFLX path — which is correct. However, if a future code path checks `accountLocalAddr6` to detect dual-stack capability, it will incorrectly conclude dual-stack is available on an IPv6-only network. Consider clearing the secondary fields after promotion:\n```suggestion\n        if (not opts.accountLocalAddr and opts.accountLocalAddr6) {\n            opts.accountLocalAddr \u003d opts.accountLocalAddr6;\n            opts.accountPublicAddr \u003d opts.accountPublicAddr6;\n            opts.accountLocalAddr6 \u003d {};\n            opts.accountPublicAddr6 \u003d {};\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "7c4e631d4c3152bd33eb055f9f5e4f378f2294b6",
