      "message": "Line 1143: 🔴 The ternary `isTcp ? PortType::TCP : PortType::UDP` is dead code — when `isTcp` is true the port is unconditionally 9 (set by the outer ternary), so `generateRandomPort` is only reached when `isTcp` is false, making the inner condition always evaluate to `PortType::UDP`. This is the same pre-existing pattern from `setupGenericReflexiveCandidates()` (line 1117), but since you\u0027re writing a new function you have an opportunity to simplify:\n```suggestion\n        uint16_t port \u003d isTcp ? 9 : upnp::Controller::generateRandomPort(PortType::UDP);\n```",
