      "message": "[critical] Line 1145: 🔴 `accountLocalAddr6_.setPort(port)` and `accountPublicAddr6_.setPort(port)` mutate the member variables in-place (same issue exists in the IPv4 version). If `setupGenericReflexiveCandidates6()` is ever called more than once, or the member addresses are read later, they\u0027ll carry the last port assigned. This is a latent bug carried from the original code, but with dual-stack there are now more call sites. Consider working on local copies:\n```suggestion\n        auto local \u003d accountLocalAddr6_;\n        auto public_ \u003d accountPublicAddr6_;\n        local.setPort(port);\n        public_.setPort(port);\n        addrList.emplace_back(local, public_);\n```",
